==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uropod
<hw>U"ro*pod</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[2d <ets>uro-</ets> +
<ets>-pod</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of the abdominal
appendages of a crustacean, especially one of the posterior ones, which
are often larger than the rest, and different in structure, and are used
chiefly in locomotion. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of <er>Crustacea</er>, and
<er>Stomapoda</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uropodal</ent>⟦br⟧
